x plus the sum of costArray[j] for each costArray in costList. Wait, the Java code is:

result.add(i * x + costList.stream().mapToLong(costArray -> costArray[j]).sum());

Here, j is the loop variable i. So for each i (the loop variable), j is set to i. Then, for each costArray in costList (each row of the 2D array), get the element at index j (i), and sum all those. So the sum is the sum of costList[k][i] for all k from 0 to N-1. So the sum for each i is sum over all rows of costList's column i. So in Fortran, for each i in 0..N-1, sum the costList(:,i) elements.
